<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Yes, there are some things that have been nerfed about the chanter class. However, chanters are still very desireable for many reason. 
<br />

<br />
Crowd control is not really as nerfed as is said I don't think. You will always find yourself in a group with a puller who can't pull or a tank with less hp then you lvl 13 ranger alt with no gear. So it is still very needed. Mez will always be needed.
<br />

<br />
Charm is something that you should learn, and learn to do well. Don't let people tell you you shouldn't charm because -insert random bullshit reason-. It can add major dps to a grp that lacks it, or just add extra dps to a group that doesn't need it for shits and giggles. A charmed pet will usually do more damage then chain nuking if you add in down time to med.
<br />

<br />
Slow and tash are a given. There are no ways around that unless you have a shammy in your grp to take care of slows.
<br />

<br />
There are a lot of tricks you will learn if you so decide to carry on your chanter. Don't get discouraged because of what you read here. Lots of the comments on these forums are exagerated a tad in my opinion. Some aren't so much as others. It is a tad boring at lower levels. Just hang in there and see what higher levels have to offer you. Best advice I can give is to wait and see. Nothing can replace a good chanter.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
