<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Of the worthwhile grouping zones in god, it works in sewers, vxed, and tipt.  It doesn't work in KT, ikkinz, or qvic.  The transition from tipt to KT is the dividing point for charm being useful and is about the halfway point of god.  After you get to the halfway point of god, charm will no longer be a useful skill for groups.  You can use it on trivial content like rcod/hollows/parts of wos to reverse charm solo, but its never again useful as a means of dps in group settings.
<br />

<br />
There IS raid charming after KT.  It can be a valuabe part of uqua if you lack dps (although with insane melee dps nowadays after the level increase it would be hard to see this being the case for anyone).  You can charm in inktuta although i've never seen a point in doing so.  Charm is an integral part of one event in txevu as well.  After that point, it seems that charm as anything but a parlour trick is completely out both for raiding and for grouping.  Maybe some people in the uberguilds have seen it farther along, but with the reduced damage tables i can't see how charming could be integrated as a real role in a raid.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
